        [
          "If you had been an 4.0 student, you probably would never have been picked for the Embrace. They never go for the noteworthy ones. Just the 'good enough' ones. Your 3.85 GPA was enough to get you into college and get you a scholarship, but it wasn't enough to protect you from the Nosferatu. You didn't have a choice as you were drawn slowly into a world of puzzles and mysteries. You solved all of them, which was good enough for your sire, who brought you into the clan. You hate it. At first you hated how ugly you were. But you're over that now. Now you hate how bitter and angry your clanmates are, how scheming and repulsive everyone is. Maybe it would have been better if you'd had a choice, you don't know. Either way, you want to hurt the people who hurt you. You've learned about a branch of the family called Anti-Tribu, and you've been selling secrets to them, quietly. You'll be killed if you're found out. Recently, the warrens in San Diego went dark, attacked by something called a Nicktuku. You have been sent there to check things out and make sure the ShreckNET servers haven't been compromised. And while you're at it, maybe make a Sabbat contact or two."
